-- Former Turkish Cypriot Leader Denktash Dies, Anatolia Reports
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-01-14T10:21:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-14/former-turkish-cypriot-leader-denktash-dies-anatolia-reports.html
Former Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktash died late yesterday at the age of 87 in a hospital in
North Cyprus, Anatolia News Agency reported.  Denktash was taken to Yakindogu University hospital on Jan.
8 for dehydration due to diarrhea, the Ankara-based state news
agency said.  Denktash, born on Jan. 27, 1924, served from 1983 until
2005 as president of the breakaway Turkish Republic of  Northern
Cyprus , which is recognized only by  Turkey .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net  